        },
        {
          "id": "th3u64v0q1",
          "type": "basic",
          "front": "<div>When you build a web application, you have to decide which development stack you want.</div><div>There are two types of Spring MVC applications:</div><div><ul><li>Web Servlet (Traditional Spring MVC)</li><li>Web Reactive</li></ul><div>Describe the&nbsp;<b>Web Reactive</b>&nbsp;development stack.</div></div>",
          "back": "<div><b>Web Reactive</b>: This is the new way of building web applications using Spring WebFlux.</div><div><ul><li>Newer, more efficient</li><li>Non-blocking</li><li>Based on the Reactive Streams API</li><li>Requires knowledge of reactive programming</li><li>Uses the <code>DispatcherHandler</code> to handle requests</li><li>Netty, Undertow, Servlet 3.1+</li><li>Specification</li></ul></div>",
          "srs": {
            "due": 1782141674473,
            "interval": 0,
            "ease": 2.5,
            "reps": 0,
            "lapses": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "3lcb7wpuf5",
          "type": "basic",
          "front": "<div>Describe the following Spring Boot auto-configuration property:</div><div><br></div><div><code>spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.xxx=???</code></div>",
          "back": "This is a placeholder for any Hibernate property that you want to set.",
          "srs": {
            "due": 1782141759617,
            "interval": 0,
            "ease": 2.5,
            "reps": 0,
            "lapses": 0
          }
        }
